the dollar dipped at one point to 126.80 yen, but closed at 127.25 yen, up 0.02 yen from monday's close. its high for the day was 127.30 yen
on the previous two trading days, the dollar lost a total of 0.97 yen
on the tokyo stock exchange, the nikkei stock average of 225 selected issues, which dropped by 110.22 points on monday, continued to fall during today's morning session, but rebounded and closed the day at 25,475.67 points, up 42.16 points, or 0.16 percent, from monday's close. volume was estimated at 1.7 billion shares in the first section
trading was active, but there weren't any real factors worth commenting on,'' said an analyst with a major brokerage. ``the market is gradually progressing toward its precrash levels and we are seeing a general consolidation,'' said the analyst, who spoke on condition of anonymity
