grain and soybean futures prices were mixed in a very narrow range this morning on the chicago board of trade
traders said there was no fresh news overnight to influence the market and little follow-through from monday's strong performance
prices were higher across the board on monday mainly because of a private forcast that farmers will be planting fewer acres of soybeans this season than had previously been thought
