general dynamics corp. announced tuesday it had established a commercial satellite-launch subsidiary in san diego
general dynamics commercial launch services inc. will provide worldwide marketing, business development, mission analysis and mission management services needed for launching u.s. and foreign satellites, said herbert f. rogers, general dynamics president
we made a very strong commitment to the satellite-launching business last summer when we decided to produce 18 atlas@centaurs (launch vehicles) for the commercial marketplace,'' rogers said. ``the establishment of general dynamics commercial launch services further reinforces this commitment.''
jack isabel, a general dynamics spokesman, said the company's main competitors in commercial-satellite launching would be mcdonnell douglas corp., martin marietta corp. and arianespace, the commercial arm of the european space agency
he said china and japan also had entered the market
dennis r. dunbar, formerly director of commercial launch services at the company's space systems division, has been named vice president and managing director of the new wholly owned subsidary. performance</head>
a new york investment partnership has filed a class action lawsuit against the chicago board options exchange, alleging it was responsible for millions of dollars of losses during the october market crash
the lawsuit, filed friday in u.s. district court in chicago, also names the options clearing corp., which processes all securities options trades in the nation
the investment partnership, m&amp;m, sued on behalf of the more than 1,000 customers it said traded in excess of $40 million worth of a november series of stock options on the standard &amp; poor's 100 stock index
the investors contend the exchange violated its rules by not halting trade in stock index options in a more timely fashion
it said the exchange operated a ``fraud and deceit upon the plaintiffs'' by failing to maintain a fair and equitable market
exchange spokesman warren moulds said it ``won't comment on pending litigation.''
george hender, executive vice president of the clearing corporation, said he couldn't comment because he had not seen the lawsuit
the lawsuit contends that on the morning of oct. 20, the day after the crash, m&amp;m put in an order to buy november put options
a put option gives the buyer the right to sell stock index contracts at a set price before the expiration date
the system in use at the exchange requires that opening trades be rotated among the various contracts, and that free trading begins only when the rotation is completed, the lawsuit said
the average length of the opening rotation is 12 to 15 minutes, it said, but in the hectic aftermath of black monday, opening rotation took 2 hours and 30 minutes
by the time m&amp;m's contracts were executed, prices ``were arbitrarily high and grossly inflated,'' the lawsuit contends
once they placed that order, they couldn't withdraw it,'' said attorney leigh r. lasky, who represents m&amp;m. ``they were locked in.''
the lawsuit contends that for the investors to have broken even, the dow jones industrial average would have had to plunge an additional 50 percent by nov. 20, the expiration date of the options
m&amp;m invested $23,400 and lost 90 percent of it, lasky said tuesday. the class of investors, which had put up more than $40 million, probably lost close to 90 percent, too, he said
the lawsuit asks that the investors be reimbursed
